						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">oRBIT2002 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Will the vram_address magically &quot;jump&quot; to the next nametable?</div><br />Yes, the name table bit will toggle.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">What will then happen at the next scanline?</div><br />At the end of the visible scanline, the X part of the scroll is copied from the temp VRAM register, so the next scanline will start at the same X coordinate as the previous one.<br /><br />If I'm not mistaken, this information is written in the diagram that was posted in this thread.<br /><br />EDIT: Yes, the &quot;hori(v) = hori(t)&quot; box Indicates when the horizontal bits of the scroll are copied from T to V.</div>

