			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The PPU performs 4 fetches for a single tile:<br /><br />- Nametable byte<br />- Attribute byte<br />- CHR low<br />- CHR high<br /><br />Each of these fetches takes 2 cycles... resulting in 8 cycles total for an 8x1 pixel image.<br />That 4-fetch pattern is repeated several times throughout the scanline.  You can think of this fetch process of &quot;loading&quot; the image, but not actually drawing it.<br /><br /><br /><em>In addition</em> to fetching, it's also outputting pixels.  1 pixel per cycle means that it'll take 8 cycles to draw an 8x1 image.<br /><br />So it takes 8 cycles to LOAD an 8x1 image.<br />And it takes 8 cycles to DRAW an 8x1 image.<br /><br />So graphics are loaded and drawn at more or less the same speed... just with a slight delay between when they're loaded and when they're actually drawn.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
